This is a custom component that listens to double tap in react native as for now there's no inbuilt method of handling the doubleTap event. The component DoubleTap will take two props(delay, toggleLike). Toggle like is any function from the calling/parent component that will contain what to happen after double click happens. An example can be adding a like when an image is tapped twice. The component containing imag will be like this: 

//toggleLike is a custom function defined in the current component where DoubleTap is being called.    
  <DoubleTap onDoubleTap={toggleLike}>
        <Image
          source={require("../assets/image.png")}
          style={styles.productImage}
        />
      </DoubleTap>

? When delay or doubletap handler(which in our case is toggleLike) function is not passed to DoubleTap delay will be set to 300ms and toggleLike will be set to null.

